Japan's Kansai Electric Power Co. Inc. said on  Thursday that its pre-tax profit fell 10.7 percent to 110.4 billion yen (1.07  billion dollars) in the year to March and forecast another fall this year.
The Osaka-based utility, the country's second-biggest power company and  one of the largest electricity generators worldwide, said revenue grew 0.2  percent from a year earlier to 2,372 billion yen.
Kansai Electric forecast a further decline in pre-tax earnings to 100  billion yen in the current year despite higher revenue of 2,420 billion yen.
